From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Varun Gupta <varun.gupta1@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 10:35:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] drm/pagemap: Provide compat for folio_free callback and
 migrate_device_pfns()

Two API differences between v7.0 and 6.6 LTS surface in drm_pagemap.c:

1. struct dev_pagemap_ops gained ::folio_free (taking struct folio *)
   and lost ::page_free (which took struct page *) in v7.0. Use
   BPM_DEV_PAGEMAP_OPS_FOLIO_FREE_NOT_PRESENT to switch the callback
   prototype and the ops slot accordingly.

2. migrate_device_pfns() was added together with the drm_pagemap core.
   On older kernels only migrate_device_pages() is available, which
   operates on a fully populated struct migrate_vma. As the only caller
   here is the shrinker-driven eviction path, gate that path with
   BPM_MIGRATE_DEVICE_PFNS_NOT_PRESENT and return -EOPNOTSUPP. The
   page-fault driven SVM migration path uses migrate_vma_setup()/
   _pages()/_finalize() and continues to work unchanged.

Signed-off-by: Varun Gupta <varun.gupta1@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c | 24 ++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
@@ -973,9 +973,22 @@ int drm_pagemap_evict_to_ram(struct drm_pagemap_devmem *devmem_allocation)
 	if (err)
 		goto err_free;
 
+#ifdef BPM_MIGRATE_DEVICE_PFNS_NOT_PRESENT
+	/*
+	 * migrate_device_pfns() is not available on older kernels
+	 * (added upstream alongside drm_pagemap). Without it, shrinker-
+	 * triggered eviction of arbitrary device PFNs cannot be performed.
+	 * Fail the eviction so the shrinker simply leaves the allocation
+	 * in place. The main SVM page-fault migration path continues to
+	 * work via migrate_vma_setup()/_pages()/_finalize().
+	 */
+	err = -EOPNOTSUPP;
+	goto err_free;
+#else
 	err = migrate_device_pfns(src, npages);
 	if (err)
 		goto err_free;
+#endif
 
 	err = drm_pagemap_migrate_populate_ram_pfn(NULL, NULL, npages, &mpages,
 						   src, dst, 0);
@@ -1138,10 +1151,17 @@ static int __drm_pagemap_migrate_to_ram(struct vm_area_struct *vas,
  * This function is a callback used to put the GPU SVM zone device data
  * associated with a page when it is being released.
  */
+#ifdef BPM_DEV_PAGEMAP_OPS_FOLIO_FREE_NOT_PRESENT
+static void drm_pagemap_folio_free(struct page *page)
+{
+	drm_pagemap_zdd_put(page->zone_device_data);
+}
+#else
 static void drm_pagemap_folio_free(struct folio *folio)
 {
 	drm_pagemap_zdd_put(folio->page.zone_device_data);
 }
+#endif
 
 /**
  * drm_pagemap_migrate_to_ram() - Migrate a virtual range to RAM (page fault handler)
@@ -1167,7 +1187,11 @@ static vm_fault_t drm_pagemap_migrate_to_ram(struct vm_fault *vmf)
 }
 
 static const struct dev_pagemap_ops drm_pagemap_pagemap_ops = {
+#ifdef BPM_DEV_PAGEMAP_OPS_FOLIO_FREE_NOT_PRESENT
+	.page_free = drm_pagemap_folio_free,
+#else
 	.folio_free = drm_pagemap_folio_free,
+#endif
 	.migrate_to_ram = drm_pagemap_migrate_to_ram,
 };
 
